Indonesia will host a summit on January 6 to address the aftermath of Asia's natural disaster.
The meeting aims to discuss the earthquake and tsunami impact, with 23 countries invited, including ASEAN members and international organizations.
Japan has deployed emergency workers to assist in Indonesia, where the death toll has risen to 94,200. International aid efforts are focused on Sumatra, with countries like China, Uzbekistan, and Bangladesh providing humanitarian assistance.
Australia pledged 1 billion Australian dollars for Indonesia's reconstruction, marking a significant step in bilateral relations.
Japan also committed to long-term reconstruction projects in Aceh and North Sumatra.
